Parent: # You can modify the data of all columns. However, the 'ChannelName' column is intended to be a hint only and gets ignored during import!
# 'Parent' contains the name of the parent module/device. This column is NOT intended to be modified!
# 'OrderNumber' contains the full order number of the device. It can be found in the Device Catalog.
# 'ModuleName' contains the name of the module for the variable that is defined in the column 'VariableName'.
# 'ChannelName' contains the human readable name of the channel. It is used only as hint and ignored during import! The important value is defined in column 'ParameterId'.
# 'ParameterId' contains the identifier of the channel (parameter) for the variable that is defined in the column 'VariableName'.
# 'Description' contains a human readable description for the variable.
# 'Unit' contains the unit for the variable.
# 'DataType' contains the data type (such as UINT) for the variable.
# 'IecAddress' contains the IEC address. Use an empty string to set the default address.
# 'VariableName' contains the name of the variable.
# 'CreateVariable' contains the boolean to determine whether a new variable should be created or the channel is mapped on an existing variable.
